cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DL

This paper deals with the creation of a bilingual semantic grammar using annotated corpora from FrameNet. This involves natural language processing and computational linguistics, which are both subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for automatic extraction of syntax, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also discusses the use of a common semantic grammar API, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL).
